818
00:59:02,160 --> 00:59:07,050
♫ <i>I'm not retreating, I won't retreat</i> ♫

819
00:59:07,050 --> 00:59:09,760
He had a very pleasant chat with his queen of darkness.

820
00:59:09,760 --> 00:59:13,000
They spoke from the bottom of their hearts and felt like they were floating in the air.

821
00:59:13,000 --> 00:59:14,430
In the end...

822
00:59:14,430 --> 00:59:17,320
What happened?

823
00:59:17,320 --> 00:59:19,790
I don't know either.

824
00:59:23,220 --> 00:59:28,130
<i>Meeting the right person at the wrong time truly is just a fairytale.</i>

825
00:59:30,230 --> 00:59:35,590
<i>I rarely have the chance to talk this much with a stranger.</i>

826
00:59:35,590 --> 00:59:39,110
<i>You seem to have filled in the missing piece in my life.</i>

827
00:59:40,480 --> 00:59:42,730
<i>Really?</i>

828
00:59:42,730 --> 00:59:47,390
<i>Are you shy...?</i>

829
00:59:47,390 --> 00:59:49,460
<i>Or afraid?</i>

830
00:59:51,170 --> 00:59:55,730
<i>Strangers are too variable. They're not good for calculations.</i>

831
00:59:55,730 --> 00:59:58,110
<i>What does that mean?</i>

832
00:59:59,060 --> 01:00:03,470
<i>Life's very short, and it can't sustain that much unpredictability.</i>

833
01:00:04,510 --> 01:00:08,130
<i>But there's a certain beauty to accidents.</i>

834
01:00:08,130 --> 01:00:13,230
<i>Many beautiful things happen by chance.</i>

835
01:00:13,890 --> 01:00:19,200
<i>In a woman's world, "If you love me, you should come find me."</i>

836
01:00:19,200 --> 01:00:25,070
<i>In a man's world, "If you love me, you won't leave."</i>

837
01:00:25,740 --> 01:00:29,390
<i>So I won't turn back.</i>

838
01:00:29,390 --> 01:00:32,050
<i>So I won't try to make someone stay.</i>

839
01:00:36,190 --> 01:00:37,950
Thank you, Uncle Xun.

840
01:00:40,050 --> 01:00:42,290
So basically, you don't know anything.

841
01:00:42,290 --> 01:00:45,810
No matter how much I asked him, he wouldn't talk.

842
01:00:45,810 --> 01:00:51,430
But from all my years of experience, any time he says there's nothing, he's hiding something.

843
01:00:51,980 --> 01:00:56,020
You're crazy. What could happen between two strangers who didn't even see each other?

844
01:00:56,020 --> 01:01:00,920
Really? If that's true, why do you stop by that restaurant every now and then?

845
01:01:00,920 --> 01:01:02,820
Because the food is good.

846
01:01:02,820 --> 01:01:04,820
Is it as good as Uncle Xun's food?

847
01:01:04,820 --> 01:01:06,980
I'm heading up. Goodnight, everyone.

848
01:01:06,980 --> 01:01:08,410
Goodnight.

849
01:01:08,410 --> 01:01:11,160
<i>The time is 11:00 p.m. on the dot.</i>

850
01:01:11,160 --> 01:01:14,670
<i>You're listening to Sophie's Night Sky.</i>

851
01:01:14,670 --> 01:01:18,320
<i>None of us are perfect, but we're all working hard. I'm Sophie.</i>

852
01:01:18,320 --> 01:01:22,410
Hey, don't you think RDR's are the worst?
(Read, Didn't Reply)

853
01:01:22,410 --> 01:01:24,330
Which woman is it this time?

854
01:01:24,330 --> 01:01:27,840
"Which woman?" This is a goddess.

855
01:01:28,790 --> 01:01:32,570
By the way, on the topic of the broken jade bracelet...

856
01:01:32,570 --> 01:01:37,690
In the end, "You didn't kill Boren, but Boren died because of you." Shouldn't you do something?

857
01:01:37,690 --> 01:01:42,460
The woman who didn't reply to you isn't possibly Wang Qiaowei, is she?

858
01:01:42,460 --> 01:01:44,800
You think she's a goddess, too.  Don't you?

859
01:01:44,800 --> 01:01:47,510
I approve of her not replying to you.

860
01:01:51,690 --> 01:01:54,920
It's better to not get involved with a strange woman like her.

861
01:01:54,920 --> 01:01:59,220
On that subject, it's true the police are partly responsible for the bracelet breaking.

862
01:01:59,220 --> 01:02:02,430
If I were her, I would request for state reimbursement.

863
01:02:02,430 --> 01:02:05,490
Yeah.

864
01:02:05,490 --> 01:02:09,750
This all happened because the police charged into the coffee shop.

865
01:02:09,750 --> 01:02:12,220
She was just an innocent casualty.

866
01:02:16,950 --> 01:02:21,800
Qiangda, why are you getting involved in police cases again?

867
01:02:21,800 --> 01:02:24,090
