876
01:03:06,550 --> 01:03:10,210
She's mocking the fact that traffic jams are always the excuse for being late.

877
01:03:11,220 --> 01:03:14,720
Oh... Is that so?

878
01:03:14,720 --> 01:03:15,840
Get off.

879
01:03:15,840 --> 01:03:18,850
I just want to know where your low-level humor lies.

880
01:03:18,850 --> 01:03:21,770
- Stop touching me.
- Ah, is it on your lower half?

881
01:03:21,770 --> 01:03:25,180
Good evening, listeners. I'm Dorothy.

882
01:03:25,180 --> 01:03:28,530
Dorothy, you know, everyone was really worried about you.

883
01:03:28,530 --> 01:03:32,440
One after another, they asked "Dorothy, where have you gone?!"

884
01:03:32,440 --> 01:03:34,410
Of course, I was still in Taipei.

885
01:03:34,410 --> 01:03:39,990
Did you think I was Dorothy from the Wizard of Oz, stuck and lost in the Land of Oz?

886
01:03:39,990 --> 01:03:41,870
Yeah.

887
01:03:41,870 --> 01:03:45,420
I want to ask our listeners a question.

888
01:03:45,420 --> 01:03:50,500
Do you know who likes going to the Land of Oz the most?

889
01:03:50,500 --> 01:03:52,550
Who?

890
01:03:52,550 --> 01:03:56,230
The answer is baseball players!

891
01:03:56,230 --> 01:03:57,970
Why?

892
01:03:57,970 --> 01:03:59,920
Because they always slide into the base.

893
01:03:59,920 --> 01:04:03,000
And then the umpire calls "Out!"

894
01:04:07,970 --> 01:04:13,070
♫ <i>If I don't love you, who would I love?</i> ♫
♫ <i>What do I mean to you?</i> ♫

895
01:04:13,070 --> 01:04:18,280
♫ <i>I'm not retreating, I won't retreat</i> ♫

896
01:04:18,280 --> 01:04:20,870
Baseball players! Because they always slide into the base.

897
01:04:20,870 --> 01:04:24,170
And then the umpire calls "Out!"

898
01:04:24,170 --> 01:04:26,650
<i>I hope everyone's not put off by this joke,</i>

899
01:04:26,650 --> 01:04:28,870
<i>and please don't tune out from our station!</i>

900
01:04:28,870 --> 01:04:32,650
<i>All right, let's listen to a good song.</i>

901
01:04:32,650 --> 01:04:36,100
He can laugh like that from such a rotten joke?

902
01:04:36,100 --> 01:04:40,410
He really likes Dorothy, for whatever reason.

903
01:04:40,410 --> 01:04:42,370
He's some kind of weirdo.

904
01:04:43,820 --> 01:04:45,810
I really don't get it.

905
01:04:45,810 --> 01:04:49,860
Why is this Dorothy person always guesting on the show?

906
01:04:49,860 --> 01:04:52,540
Because her sincerity is so interesting.

907
01:04:56,990 --> 01:05:00,500
Uncle Xun, turn that off or I'm going to break it.

908
01:05:03,110 --> 01:05:05,030
Forget it.

909
01:05:05,030 --> 01:05:06,930
What?

910
01:05:06,930 --> 01:05:09,510
You got a new job?

911
01:05:09,510 --> 01:05:12,040
I did.

912
01:05:12,040 --> 01:05:14,940
But I also have a big debt now.

913
01:05:14,940 --> 01:05:18,560
This Dorothy isn't a simple person.

914
01:05:18,560 --> 01:05:21,430
She's a cheerful and optimistic girl.

915
01:05:21,430 --> 01:05:22,800
I see.

916
01:05:25,160 --> 01:05:27,650
She said she was caught in a fire when she was young.

917
01:05:27,650 --> 01:05:31,460
Her back and chest are covered in burn scars.

918
01:05:31,460 --> 01:05:35,900
When the Furmosa Fun Coast explosion happened, she shared a lot of her rehabilitation experiences.

919
01:05:35,900 --> 01:05:38,310
It touched a lot of people.

920
01:05:41,070 --> 01:05:45,960
Who would have thought that our cold Master Qiang had such a sentimental side?

921
01:05:45,960 --> 01:05:49,120
You sure talk a lot of crap. If you're done, go home.

922
01:05:49,120 --> 01:05:51,750
Be happy!

923
01:05:51,750 --> 01:05:55,910
Being happy's the most important; otherwise, you start spewing crap.

924
01:05:56,970 --> 01:05:59,250
Thank you for the delicious meal, Uncle Xun.

925
01:05:59,250 --> 01:06:01,330
I'll take my leave.

926
01:06:01,330 --> 01:06:03,500
Let's go home.

927
01:06:04,330 --> 01:06:07,580
- Let's go.
- You go first.

928
01:06:08,560 --> 01:06:10,780
Bye, Uncle Xun.

929
01:06:15,380 --> 01:06:19,910
<i>When I'm in a bad mood, or I feel upset about something,</i>

930
